children.subject: Personally I think Stat 133 is not only useless with the CS background you have but also poorly structured and very boring, especially if you will eventually take Data 100. I dropped the course one week into the semester because the lectures were too painful to sit through. Data 100 should be fine for you without Data 8.

I’m taking Ling 100 this semester and yeah I think the workload is pretty low. Although it is considered a cs tech elective, I haven’t seen more than 5 minutes of code or even applications in coding so I would say only take it if you are interested in linguistics. It is a pretty interesting breadth though; the content is stuff I can bring up in conversations

history.content: I think I am going to have a decently difficult schedule next semester, so I was wondering if people had any suggestions on tech electives that are interesting and are pretty low workload, or at least not high workload. I know some people have suggested Ling 100 (taught by Keith Johnson), I have heard mixed things about Stat 133, mixed reviews on the workload of Stat 140, UGBA 103 and 102a/b seem interesting, and I was wondering if Data 100 would be a lot of work without Data 8 and without a stats background after having taken 61A/B, 70, and some upper divs like 170 and 188. Any suggestions or insights into these classes would be great! Thanks a ton.
history.subject: Suggestions on Interesting Tech Electives that are pretty low workload?
